@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor User
participant "VS Code" as VSCode
participant "Extension\n(extension.ts)" as Extension
participant "CtFlowEditorProvider" as EditorProvider
participant "Webview UI\n(React)" as Webview
participant "Flow Component\n(Flow.tsx)" as FlowComponent
participant "NodeMenuPanel" as NodeMenu
participant "CompilePanel" as CompilePanel
participant "Compiler\n(index.ts)" as Compiler
participant "Graph Builder\n(graph.ts)" as Graph
participant "Node Compilers\n(cypress/*)" as NodeCompilers
participant "Cypress Engine" as Cypress
participant "Firebase\n(Collaboration)" as Firebase

== Extension Initialization ==
User -> VSCode: Open .ctflow file
VSCode -> Extension: Activate extension
Extension -> EditorProvider: Register custom editor
EditorProvider -> Webview: Create webview panel
Webview -> FlowComponent: Initialize React Flow
FlowComponent -> Webview: Render visual editor
Webview -> VSCode: Request initial data
VSCode -> Webview: Send .ctflow file content
Webview -> FlowComponent: Load nodes and edges

== Visual Test Flow Creation ==
User -> FlowComponent: Interact with canvas
User -> NodeMenu: Drag and drop node
NodeMenu -> FlowComponent: Add node to flow
activate FlowComponent
FlowComponent -> FlowComponent: Update nodes state
FlowComponent -> Webview: Render new node
deactivate FlowComponent

User -> FlowComponent: Connect nodes with edges
activate FlowComponent
FlowComponent -> FlowComponent: Update edges state
FlowComponent -> Webview: Render connections
deactivate FlowComponent

User -> FlowComponent: Configure node properties
FlowComponent -> Webview: Update node data

== Real-time Collaboration (Optional) ==
FlowComponent -> Firebase: Sync flow changes
Firebase --> FlowComponent: Broadcast to collaborators
Firebase -> Webview: Update from remote changes
Webview -> FlowComponent: Merge remote updates

== Save Test Flow ==
User -> Webview: Save flow
Webview -> VSCode: Send flow data via VS Code API
VSCode -> Extension: Process save request
Extension -> Extension: Serialize to YAML
Extension -> VSCode: Write .ctflow file

== Compile to Cypress Code ==
User -> CompilePanel: Click compile
CompilePanel -> Compiler: Compile flow to Cypress
activate Compiler
Compiler -> Graph: Build graph from nodes/edges
Graph -> Graph: Validate flow structure
Graph -> Compiler: Return graph representation
Compiler -> Compiler: Traverse graph (DFS/BFS)

loop For each node in traversal order
    Compiler -> NodeCompilers: Find appropriate compiler
    NodeCompilers -> NodeCompilers: Compile node to Cypress code
    NodeCompilers -> Compiler: Return code snippet
    Compiler -> Compiler: Append to output
end

Compiler -> CompilePanel: Return compiled Cypress code
deactivate Compiler
CompilePanel -> Webview: Display generated code
Webview -> User: Show Cypress test script

== Execute Cypress Tests ==
User -> CompilePanel: Run tests
CompilePanel -> VSCode: Request test execution
VSCode -> Cypress: Execute generated test script
activate Cypress
Cypress -> Cypress: Run test commands
Cypress -> VSCode: Stream test results
deactivate Cypress
VSCode -> Webview: Display test results
Webview -> User: Show test outcome

== Custom Node Management ==
User -> FlowComponent: Add custom node
FlowComponent -> Webview: Render CustomNodeRender
User -> Webview: Configure custom node
Webview -> Extension: Export custom node config
Extension -> VSCode: Save custom node definition

== CTFlow Recorder Node ==
User -> FlowComponent: Use CTFlowRecorderNode
FlowComponent -> Firebase: Start recording session
User -> FlowComponent: Record actions
FlowComponent -> Firebase: Store recorded actions
User -> FlowComponent: Replay actions
FlowComponent -> Firebase: Retrieve recorded actions
Firebase -> FlowComponent: Return action sequence
FlowComponent -> Webview: Execute recorded flow

@enduml
